// WebSocket Terminal Handler
// Manages WebSocket connections for PTY-backed terminal sessions. Handles open,
// message, close, and error lifecycle events, routing input/resize messages to
// the PTY manager and detaching on disconnect.

WebSocket messages follow a typed JSON protocol.
Client sends: input (keystroke data) or resize (cols + rows).
Server sends: output (terminal data), exit (process exit code), or error (message string).

FUNCTION sendError(ws, message)
  Serialize an error message as JSON and send it to the WebSocket client.
  Swallow any errors that occur during the send (e.g. socket already closed).

---

FUNCTION handleTerminalOpen(ws) -> void                                    EXPORT
  CALLS: ptyManager.attach (terminal/index)
  Read sessionId from ws.data (set by server during WebSocket upgrade).
  IF sessionId is missing, send error and close the connection.
  Attach the WebSocket to the PTY session via ptyManager, deferring buffer
  replay until the first resize message (deferReplay: true).
  IF attach fails, send an error message describing the failure and close.

---

FUNCTION handleTerminalMessage(ws, message) -> void                        EXPORT
  CALLS: ptyManager.write (terminal/index), ptyManager.resize (terminal/index)
  Read sessionId from ws.data. IF missing, send error and return.
  Parse message as JSON. IF parsing fails, send error and return.
  IF message type is "input", forward the data string to ptyManager.write.
  IF message type is "resize", forward cols and rows to ptyManager.resize.
  IF type is unrecognized, send error naming the unknown type.

---

FUNCTION handleTerminalClose(ws) -> void                                   EXPORT
  CALLS: ptyManager.detach (terminal/index)
  Read sessionId from ws.data. IF missing, return immediately.
  Detach the WebSocket from the PTY session via ptyManager.

---

FUNCTION handleTerminalError(ws, error) -> void                            EXPORT
  CALLS: ptyManager.detach (terminal/index)
  Log the error with the sessionId.
  IF sessionId is present, detach the WebSocket from the PTY session.
